CatDescriptText: Hazel Pearsall, secretary to Congressman Moorehead, 1005 Sheffield Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, pg. 6 with question: "With Mayor Lawrence performing his duties as Governor in Harrisburg, do you believe the Democratic party in Pittsburgh will be weakened by his absence?" answer reads: "Definitely not: in fact, I think that it will strengthen it.  The reason I say this is because the Democratic party is a very powerful party and the working man's party."
